63c786051","tid":740783,"uid":89514,"like":3,"dislike":12,"score":-9,"quote":{"pid":"98d5fb6e730aa0d12b8264ac4084051cb73f340f","tid":740783,"uid":178317,"like":5,"dislike":29,"score":-24,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T07:28:37.000Z","msg":"其實google都幾無聊，改完個名咁又點？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n放多啲時間做下研究新技術好過啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T07:41:24.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T07:58:23.000Z","msg":"睇youtube個comment<br />\n<br />\nFew things:<br />\n-The first app you tested on Android was using Vuforia, which is not ARCore. Vuforia works by capturing a 2D surface, kinda like taking a picture, and monitoring the transformations of that picture to determine the angle the camera is looking at the surface with, which is less reliable than ARCore or ARKit.<br />\n<br />\n-The Stack AR apps you tested were different apps from different developers. The Android app was, again, using Fuvoria which is again, not ARCore.<br />\n<br />\n-The apps that didn't work on the S9 but were using ARCore were developed for an older version of ARCore while you had the newer version installed. The glitching was basically a compatibility issue between the older app and the newer ARCore.<br />\n<br />\nAlso,<br />\n<br />\nARCore and ARKit preform basically the same. They can both<br />\n<br />\n-Detect horizontal and vertical planes (Although ARCore detects angled surfaces as well)<br />\n<br />\n-Track the motion of the device using feature points and the device's accelerometer<br />\n<br />\n-Estimate lighting using the camera view<br />\n<br />\nBottom line:<br />\nThey're both great and preform basically the same (although ARCore does allow angled planes which ARKit doesn't). So in the end it really doesn't matter and AR compatibility shouldn't influence which of these devices you pick.﻿<br />\n<br />\n仲有係Apple做跟尾狗"},{"pid":"ad7345fa1123620e1237b2e786f080a8e0b34b1e","tid":740783,"uid":194606,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"fc8300905461c2beb14c3dfe4db1ba2087cbe0b6","tid":740783,"uid":35542,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"6712e79d6477fc67c8ad8636646406063c786051","tid":740783,"uid":89514,"like":3,"dislike":12,"score":-9,"quote":{"pid":"98d5fb6e730aa0d12b8264ac4084051cb73f340f","tid":740783,"uid":178317,"like":5,"dislike":29,"score":-24,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T07:28:37.000Z","msg":"其實google都幾無聊，改完個名咁又點？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n放多啲時間做下研究新技術好過啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T07:41:24.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T07:58:23.000Z","msg":"睇youtube個comment<br />\n<br />\nFew things:<br />\n-The first app you tested on Android was using Vuforia, which is not ARCore. Vuforia works by capturing a 2D surface, kinda like taking a picture, and monitoring the transformations of that picture to determine the angle the camera is looking at the surface with, which is less reliable than ARCore or ARKit.<br />\n<br />\n-The Stack AR apps you tested were different apps from different developers. The Android app was, again, using Fuvoria which is again, not ARCore.<br />\n<br />\n-The apps that didn't work on the S9 but were using ARCore were developed for an older version of ARCore while you had the newer version installed. The glitching was basically a compatibility issue between the older app and the newer ARCore.<br />\n<br />\nAlso,<br />\n<br />\nARCore and ARKit preform basically the same. They can both<br />\n<br />\n-Detect horizontal and vertical planes (Although ARCore detects angled surfaces as well)<br />\n<br />\n-Track the motion of the device using feature points and the device's accelerometer<br />\n<br />\n-Estimate lighting using the camera view<br />\n<br />\nBottom line:<br />\nThey're both great and preform basically the same (although ARCore does allow angled planes which ARKit doesn't). So in the end it really doesn't matter and AR compatibility shouldn't influence which of these devices you pick.﻿<br />\n<br />\n仲有係Apple做跟尾狗"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T08:04:32.000Z","msg":"好中肯 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 原來個App唔係用ARCore <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"96f1e4d037404359561515a54a31969ae7202401","tid":740783,"uid":89514,"like":3,"dislike":15,"score":-12,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T08:08:45.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"bd87cc88b718b4cc9e95a735f6fec2d4ca484b9e","tid":740783,"uid":60695,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T10:27:25.000Z","msg":"鹹嘅甜品仲係唔係甜品<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"8bba3a9a00164f8b9b6400c885714c3ddf5b4b23","tid":740783,"uid":158977,"like":5,"dislike":1,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"96f1e4d037404359561515a54a31969ae7202401","tid":740783,"uid":89514,"like":3,"dislike":15,"score":-12,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-13T08:08:45.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-07-14T11:25:07.000Z","msg":"抄<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <br />\n你好撚柒<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/wet.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 以為係Apple發明?<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"9a5aba25ac1f9f2f2ad18ebf8fd94c76230e4f28","tid":740783,"uid":2766,"like":0,"dislike":10,"score":-10,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-14T11:51:07.000Z","msg":"晒時間改埋d食物名 on撚9<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"006c67250499e003a4ff8a6a9b08370ef4e6ac3d","tid":740783,"uid":35542,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"quote":{"pid":"9a5aba25ac1f9f2f2ad18ebf8fd94c76230e4f28","tid":740783,"uid":2766,"like":0,"dislike":10,"score":-10,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-07-14T11:51:07.000Z","msg":"晒時間改埋d食物名 on撚9<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"ci